block content
  #main.jumbotron
    .container
      .row
        .col-xs-12.col-sm-12.col-md-12.col-lg-12
          h1 About Project 
          p(style='margin-bottom:0px;padding-bottom:0px;') Project Mind Research is being developed by Brandon Laurence Clark for his Master in Software Engineering degree at California State University Fullerton.
          ul.nav.nav-pills(role="tablist", style='margin-top:0px;padding-top:0px;')
            li(role="presentation", style='padding:0px; padding-right:20px;')
              h4 About      
            li(role="presentation")
              a.text-muted(href="#project") » Mind Research
            li(role="presentation")
              a.text-muted(href="#author") » Author
            li(role="presentation")
              a.text-muted(href="#amse",style='margin-left:0px;padding-left:0px;') » Degree
  section
    #project.container
      .row
        .col-xs-12.col-sm-12.col-md-12.col-lg-12
          h3 About Project Mind Research
          h4  
            img(src='/images/site/mind-research.png', style='width:200px;float:left;margin-bottom:2px;margin-right:10px;')  
            |  Vision  
          p This product is intended for researchers to compose, conduct and analyze survey questionnaires. Users will be accessing web based services in both desktop and mobile environments. In addition to providing visual interface service a Web Application Program Interface ( Web API ) should be provided to developers.  
          p Architecture for this software should be cloud based to maximize resource availability. This architecture is to support a software base that communicates between services offered to users. Software is to built by component when possible to maximize modifiability and scalability.  
          p This service is to include a statistical formula tool for designing data measurements based on a questionnaires feedback. Features of the product should include real-time data interaction and an ability to add additional analysis tools and services to an existing account. Social integrations should be made where possible to enhance the user experience.
          p A project deadline has been set for May 10, 2015 and will be managed though a modified Agile process known as SCRUM.
          br
          br
        .col-xs-12.col-sm-6.col-md-6.col-lg-6
          h4
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-cloud  
            |  Cloud Management Plan 
          p An in house cloud management system will be setup to use the Ubuntu Server 14.04 LTS operating system to implement the product. MAAS bare metal provision software and Juju service orchestration software will be integrated to manage the cloud service environment. 
          p Amazon web services will be used in place of MAAS during development.  Amazon works well out of the box for the projects overall management, testing and work product deliveries.  
          br
          br
        .col-xs-12.col-sm-6.col-md-6.col-lg-6
          h4  
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-retweet  
            |   Project Management Plan  
          p To aid in the process of fulfilling the requirements a project management component will be developed to manage time and task based on the SCRUM Life Cycle principles. Project management will provide progress and schedule statistics.  
          p The project management component will be integrated with Github services for version and source control of project components source code. 
          br
          br
        .col-xs-12.col-sm-12.col-md-12.col-lg-12
          h4 Questionnaire Management Plan
          .col-xs-12.col-sm-4.col-md-4.col-lg-4
            h5 
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-leaf  
            |   Create  
            p Users will generate questionnaires based on a three question type model. Question models will be single response, multiple response and open response.
            p Single and multiple response question will be used to produce quantitative data.  Open response questions are used to create qualitative measurements.
            p Questionnaire responses can be limited to a confined period or open ended.
            br 
          .col-xs-12.col-sm-4.col-md-4.col-lg-4
            h5 
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-globe  
            |   Conduct  
            p Send survey questionnaires out to desired user pools over Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn, email and text communication channels.
            p Survey takers will have an option to keep their response anonymous.
            p All survey responses will be open to the public while survey management is limited to conductor or the survey questionnaires.
            br 
          .col-xs-12.col-sm-4.col-md-4.col-lg-4
            h5 
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-eye-open  
            |   Analyze  
            p Users view real-time statistics responses.  A standard report format will be provided and available in XLS or PDF format.
            p A descriptive statistic formulation tool will allow users to write statistical formulas based on response data.  
            P Qualitative analysis will currently provide a built in Sentiment analysis using the AFINN-111 standard word list.
            br 
            br
            br
            br
          br
