          p My bachelors degree is in Business Information Systems and Decision Systems. 
          p I have a strong management background that has provided me with a great number of skill sets. My professional history contains five plus years of team management and self management positions.
          p My programming history has been hobby based since 1996. I have worked with numerous programming languages and and have gained a strong understanding of language and software paradigms. Currently my proficiency is in using the Node.js framework and many of its packages.
          p My software engineering experience has been primarily academic with focuses on the Compatibility Maturity Model and Agile principles and processes.
          p I enjoy traveling with my wife around the world. Scuba diving is one of my favorite activities along with Frisbee Golf. I love the outdoors just as much as my geeky passions for technology.
